        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 11:11AM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 1111 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Cometa, or 13 miles southwest of La Pryor, moving
northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Pryor, Batesville, and Washer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
